Petroleum distributor OLA Energy Kenya is targeting to open 100 petroleum dealer outlets from its current 80 by 2019 as part of its profitability plan. This is part of its turn around plan that saw the distributor rebrand from OiLibya Group to OLA Energy Group. The rebranding will be implemented in 1,100 stations in the Group’s 17 countries operating across Africa. Locally, Libya Oil Kenya Limited will change its name to OLA Energy Kenya Limited. ‘‘OLA Energy will allow us to expand our involvement in the energy sector under a stronger, and more modern international brand,” said chief executive Duncan Murashiki. He said the firm hopes to leverage on the governments Sh2 billion Mwananchi Gas Project aimed at increasing use of Liquefied petroleum gas among Kenyans.